o mit Ergebnissen für angrenzende Disziplinen der Theologie, Geschichte und Kunstgeschichte aufwarten.  a"Tagzeitentexte" are texts structured according to the prayer schedules used by clergy for daily services. They provide special insight into the structure and usage of medieval prayer-books, given their prominence as one of the largest groups of texts. For the first time, this study provides a scholarly survey of these diverse texts.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aGebetbuchliteratur. 4aGeistliche Literatur. 4aMittelalter. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aMiddle Ages.  aprayer book.  aspiritual literature.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU0 cprintz978311060123740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311060124440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110601244423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110601244.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DKUb2021